file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: Table of selected extracted fields from the final VCF of combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters.

file_description: Table of selected extracted fields from the final VCF of combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

Variants were then called with GATK Haplotypecaller.

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters.

file_description: Filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

file_description: Table of selected extracted fields from the final VCF of combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: Full unannotated SNP and InDEL variants called. Raw reads trimmed with CutAdapt, mapped with BWA to GRCh38, and primer sequence was removed with primerclip. design_description: xGen(TM) Sample Identification (ID) Amplicon Panel

file_description: VCF with filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

file_description: VCF with filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters.

Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. file_description: VCF with filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

file_description: Table of selected extracted fields from the final VCF of combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: VCF with SNP, insertions, and deletions from Mutect2 calling and FilterMutectCalls filtering. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls

file_description: Filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: Table of selected extracted fields from the final VCF of combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF
design_description: IDT xGen Exome v2 hyb panel

file_description: SNP variants called that are not part of the xGen Sample ID amplicon panel. Variants were then called with GATK Haplotypecaller.

Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters.

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters.

file_description: VCF with filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

file_description: VCF with filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

file_description: Table of selected extracted fields from the final VCF of combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: Table of selected extracted fields from the final VCF of combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: VCF with SNP, insertions, and deletions from Mutect2 calling and FilterMutectCalls filtering. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls

Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID

file_description: BAM alignment file for BAM derived from raw reads trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. design_description: IDT xGen Exome v2 hyb panel

file_description: VCF with combined SNP and insertions and deletions following filtering by FilterMutectCalls, depth and quality filters and annoated with dbSNP IDs and SNPeff. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID and snpEFF

file_description: Filtered insertion and deletion calls with dbSNP IDs. Raw reads were first trimmed for quality using a custom python script. Human / mouse disambiguation of quality filtered reads was done with Xenome. Human specifc reads were mapped with BWA to GRCh38. Duplicate reads were marked with Picard MarkDuplicates. Base recalibration was then done and applied with GATK. Variants were called with GATK Mutect2 in tumor only mode, reads were called against a panel of normal samples from the 1000 genome project and germline reference from the GnomAD project both references provided by GATK. Variants were soft filtered with FilterMutectCalls, and depth and quality filters. Variant were annotated with dbsnpID
